        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] in accordance with Mal. 3:23 (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Malachi 4:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), on which the Jews founded the expectation that Elias, who had been taken up into heaven, would appear again in bodily form and introduce the Messiah (Wetstein on this passage; Lightfoot on ",
        "children": []
